eval.reason:
The task was to find help on withdrawing an article from ArXiv if the submission has not yet been announced. 

The final screenshot clearly shows a section titled "Withdrawing an article," which explains the process for submissions that are not yet announced. It mentions going to the user page and selecting the "Delete" or "Unsubmit" icon. This matches the information given in the result response, confirming it is accurate and complete.

Therefore, the task has been successfully accomplished.

**Verdict: SUCCESS**

agent_answer: I found the information on how to withdraw an article from ArXiv. If your submission has not yet become publicly available, you can delete or delay it by going to your user page and selecting the Delete or Unsubmit icon. A withdrawal will create a new version of the paper marked as withdrawn, which does not link directly to the full text. If your submission has been announced, it cannot be completely removed, but it can be marked as withdrawn. Please refer to the provided screenshot for detailed instructions.

task.question: Visit ArXiv Help on how to withdraw an article if the submission is not yet announced.
task.answer: If your submission has not yet become publicly available you may delete or delay it. To do either of these things go to your user page and select either the Delete or Unsubmit icon.
